(^{k}_{l})
\phi:M \to N
\phi^{*}A
v_{1}, \dots , v_{k} \in M_{p}
\lambda_{1},\dots, \lambda_{l} \in M_{p}^{*}
[\phi^{*}A(p)](v_{1},\dots, v_k,\lambda_1, \dots ,\lambda_l)
 =A(\phi(p))(\phi_{*}v_1,\dots ,\phi_{*}v_k,
(\phi^{-1})^{*}\lambda_1,\dots,(\phi^{-1})^{*}\lambda_l).
L_{x_1+x_2}A=L_{x_1}A+L_{x_2}A.
(L_{x}A)(p)=lim_{h\to 0} [(\phi_{h}^{*}A)(p)-A(p)]/h.
